1. *Isothermal slope:* Under constant temperature, the ideal gas follows $P V = C$. Taking the derivative:
     $ P d V + V d P = 0 => (d P / d V)_"iso" = - P / V $

  2. *Adiabatic slope:* Under adiabatic conditions ($Q=0$), an ideal gas follows $P V^gamma = C$. Differentiating this relation yields:
     $ V^gamma d P + P gamma V^(gamma - 1) d V = 0 $
     Dividing the entire expression by $V^(gamma - 1)$:
     $ V d P + P gamma d V = 0 => (d P / d V)_"adi" = -gamma P / V $

  Comparing the expressions demonstrates that:
  $ (d P / d V)_"adi" = gamma (d P / d V)_"iso" $